Key Match Events: Trae Young scored 33 points and had nine assists.
Jalen Johnson scored 19 points on 8-13 shooting.
Onyeka Okongwu had a double-double with 14 points and 11 rebounds.
Anthony Davis returned to the lineup and recorded an 18 point and 18 rebound double-double.
Austin Reaves scored 20 points and had seven assists.
LeBron James scored 30 points and had eight assists.
Dalton Knecht hit three three-pointers in the second quarter.
Dyson Daniels forced three turnovers in the third quarter.
LeBron James scored 10 points in six minutes during the fourth quarter.
Pre-Game Insights: The Hawks got Bogdan Bogdanovic and Jalen Johnson back in the lineup against the Lakers.
Post-Match Reflections: The Hawks' defense was disorganized and struggled with help defense and perimeter defense.
DeAndre Hunter had a poor game, scoring only 3 points on 1-12 shooting from the field and 0-6 from deep.
